It is important to include on the first page of your guide the following sections: Prerequisites, What you'll learn, What you'll need, and What you'll build. Remember, part of the purpose of a Sigma Quickstart is that the reader will have **built** something by the end of the tutorial; this means that actual code needs to be included (not just pseudo-code).

