## Metadata Configuration
Duration: 2

It is important to set the correct metadata for your Sigma Quickstart. The metadata contains all the information required for listing and publishing your guide and includes the following:

- **summary**: This is a sample Sigma QuickStart 
  - This should be a short, 1 sentence description of your guide. This will be visible on the main landing page. 
- **id**: sample 
  - make sure to match the id here with the name of the file, all one word.
- **categories**: data-science 
  - You can have multiple categories, but the first one listed is used for the icon.
- **environments**: web 
  - `web` is default. If this will be published for a specific event or  conference, include it here.
- **status**: Published
  - (`Draft`, `Published`, `Deprecated`, `Hidden`) to indicate the progress and whether the QuickStart is ready to be published. `Hidden` implies the QuickStart is for restricted use, should be available only by direct URL, and should not appear on the main landing page.
- **feedback link**: https://github.com/sigmacomputing/sigmaquickstarts/issues
- **tags**: Getting Started, Data Science, Twitter 
  - Add relevant  tags to make your QuickStart easily found and SEO friendly.
- **authors**: Phil Ballai
  - Indicate the author(s) of this specific QuickStart.

